description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to an Assessment Day on Friday 20th November 2020 held at Carew House in Bodmin. Please note this will be either a morning or afternoon session to be confirmed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is for a Band 5 Community Nurse on a fixed term contract (Oct 2020 to March 2021) working full time hours within our Community Nursing Teams across various areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These areas are&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bodmin &amp; Par&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Liskeard &amp; Looe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;North Coast Cluster (Wadebridge/Port Isaac) &amp; Stratton&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Launceston &amp; Callington &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced, caring, motivated community nurse to join our Community Nurse teams. You should be flexible, and possess commitment to team working, and innovative delivery of excellent standards of care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; You should also have an understanding of the changing climate of care delivery in the community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to travel independently across the area to fulfil the requirements of the post is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLucy Clement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job titleNorth Integrated Community Manage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rEmail addresslucyclement@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01208 834413&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Hegarty fiona.hegarty@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
